144|title=Altair Agencja Lotnicza|website=Altair.com.pl}}</ref>\n| [[File:Mini-Beryl wz96 PICT0015.JPG|150px]]\n| compact assault rifle (carbine)\n| {{Flagu|Poland}}\n| 10 test units (wz. 1996C)<ref name=\"altair.com.pl\"/>\n|-\n| [[M16 rifle|M16A1]]<ref name=\"ewen2005\">Jane's Special Forces Recognition Guide, Ewen Southby-Tailyour (2005) p. 446</ref>\n| [[File:M16A1 brimob.jpg|150px]]\n| Assault Rifle \n| {{Flagu|United States}} \n|\n|-\n| [[FN FNC]]<ref name=\"jones2009\"/> \n| [[File:FNC IMG 1527.jpg|150px]]\n| Assault Rifle\n| {{Flagu|Belgium}} \n| \n|-\n| [[Beretta AR70/90]]<ref name=\"jones2009\"/>\n| [[File:Scheda2c.JPG|150px]]\n| Assault Rifle\n| {{Flagu|Italy}} \n| \n|-\n| [[Daewoo Precision Industries K2|Daewoo K2]]<ref name=\"K2 export\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.segye.com/Articles/News/Politics/Article.asp?aid=20110531004060&subctg1=&subctg2= |title=Archived copy |access-date=21 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314043323/http://www.segye.com/Articles/News/Politics/Article.asp?aid=20110531004060&subctg1=&subctg2= |archive-date=14 March 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n| [[File:Daewoo K2 rifle 1.jpg|150px]]\n| Assault Rifle\n| {{Flagu|South Korea}} \n|33,000 Units have been bought\n|-\n| [[AK-47|OBJ-006]]\n| [[File:AK-47 type II Part DM-ST-89-01131.jpg|150px]]\n| Assault Rifle \n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| Produced as ''OBJ-006''.<ref>[http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/200610/02/eng20061002_308128.html \"Nigeria to mass-produce Nigerian version of AK-47 rifles.\"] Retrieved on 5 October 2008.</ref><ref>[http://www.dicon.gov.ng/military1.html \"DICON \u2013 Defence Industry Corp. of Nigeria\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227081924/http://www.dicon.gov.ng/military1.html |date=27 December 2013 }} Retrieved on 23 June 2012.</ref>\n|-\n| [[AKM]]<ref name=\"rottman\">Rottman, Gordon (2011). ''The AK-47 Kalashnikov series assault rifles''. Great Britain: Osprey Publishing. {{ISBN|978-1-8