ade>{{cite web|url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/armstrade/page/trade_register.php |title=Trade Registers |website=Armstrade.sipri.org |accessdate=2014-04-20}}</ref> \n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Recoilless rifle]]s'''\n|-\n| [[M40 recoilless rifle|M40]]<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n| [[File:Rcl106lat2.jpg|150px]]\n| Anti-tank weapon\n| {{Flagu|United States}} \n| \n|-\n| [[Carl Gustav recoilless rifle|Carl Gustav]]\n| [[File:M3E1.jpg|150px]]\n| Anti-tank weapon\n| {{Flagu|Sweden}} \n| 30 in service.<ref name=\"jones2009\"/>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Rocket-propelled grenade]]s'''\n|-\n| [[RPG-7]]\n| [[File:RPG-7V1 grenade launcher - RaceofHeroes-part2-22.jpg|150px]]\n| Anti-tank weapon \n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} <br> {{Flagu|Nigeria}}\n| Some of Nigerian manufacture.<ref>[http://www.dicon.gov.ng/milproduct4.html Defense Industries Corporation of Nigeria] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227073944/http://www.dicon.gov.ng/milproduct4.html |date=27 December 2013 }} Retrieved on 1 May 2013.</ref>\n|}\n\n===Armoured fighting vehicles===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Photo\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Type\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Country of Origin\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|In Service\n! style=\"text-align: left;\"|Notes\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Main battle tank]]s'''\n|-\n| [[VT-4]]\n| \n| Main Battle Tank\n| {{Flagu|China}} \n| \n| Delivered in April 2020.<ref>https://www.defenceweb.co.za/featured/nigerian-military-receives-tanks-artillery-from-china/</ref>\n|-\n| [[T-72]]\n| [[File:ParkPatriot2015part2-18.jpg|170px]]\n| Main Battle Tank\n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} \n| 77<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.naij.com/517069-photo-documents-contains-list-weapons-allegedly-obtained-jonathans-government.html|title=PHOTO: This Document Contains List of Weapons Alleg