ret armoured car|Ferret]]\n| [[File:Ferret-Scout-Car-18EA24.jpg|170px]]\n| Scout Car\n| {{Flagu|United Kingdom}}\n| 25<ref name=\"nigeriastudy\"/>\n| 40 delivered.<ref name=trade/>\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Infantry fighting vehicle]]s'''\n|-\n| [[BMP-1]]\n| [[File:BWP-1 Baltops 2016 0283.jpg|170px]]\n| Infantry Fighting Vehicle\n| {{Flagu|Soviet Union}} \n| 4<ref name=\"ZA2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38580:recent-nigerian-military-acquisitions&catid=50:Land&Itemid=105|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6XiVrDyDS?url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38580:recent-nigerian-military-acquisitions&catid=50:Land&Itemid=105|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 April 2015|title=Recent Nigerian military acquisitions|author=Guy Martin|website=Webcitation.org|accessdate=30 March 2015}}</ref>\n| ''BVP-1'' variant.\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Armoured personnel carrier]]s'''\n|-\n| [[Saurer 4K 4FA]]\n| [[File:SPz A1 Saurer (2).jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{flagu|Austria}}\n| 250<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n| 300 delivered.<ref name=\"nigeriastudy\">{{cite book|last=Metz|first=Helen Chapin|title=Nigeria: A Country Study|pages=336\u2013349}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[MT-LB]]\n| [[File:Soviet MT-LB.JPEG|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Poland}} \n| 67<ref name=trade/>\n| Sourced from Poland.\n|-\n| [[Mowag Piranha]] I 6x6\n| [[File:Piranha Meiringen.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Switzerland}}\n| 110<ref name=\"ZA\"/>\n| \n|-\n| [[BTR-4]]\n| [[File:BTR-4E in Kyiv.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Ukraine}}\n| \n| BTR-4 with Grom module\n|-\n| [[BTR-3]]\n| [[File:BTR3.jpg|170px]]\n| Armoured Personnel Carrier\n| {{Flagu|Ukraine}}\n| 47<ref name=trade/>\n| ''BTR-3U \"Guardian\"'' variant.\n|-\n| [[BTR-70]]\n| [[File:2015-05-05. \u0420\